    "Body": " Ripple is looking for a learning and talent development professional to design, deliver, and scale learning programs including manager development, professional skills, and onboarding. This role reports into the Head of Learning and Development. The ideal candidate has deep expertise in experiential learning, facilitation, coaching, and program management with subject matter expertise in both management capability and professional skill development and a passion for transformation and culture. What You'll Do Program Design: Design high-impact talent programs for manager capability and professional skills informed by business needs and industry research. Work with new managers and managers new to Ripple to ensure foundational leadership skills. Work closely with business leadership and broader People teams, ensuring programs embody our values. Program Management: Execute talent development programs end-to-end; create clear program project plans, stakeholder maps, and manage execution. Change Management & Communication: Leverage change management methodologies to ensure global program adoption. Develop and deploy communication plans. Facilitation & Delivery: ability to engage learners, facilitate dialog, tell compelling stories, and deliver a variety of content both in a classroom and virtual setting. Evaluation and Analytics: Report on appropriate talent metrics; identify key insights to inform future actions and decision making. Continuous Improvement: assess and evolve programs based on feedback and metrics. What We're Looking For 5-7 years working in talent development 5-7 years working in program management with experience designing and scaling programs Strong stakeholder management and communication skills Experience facilitating learning through classes or workshops Excellent teaming skills Detail-oriented and organized and comfortable with technology including Google Calendar, Slides, Docs, etc. and LMS technology Desire and ability to travel to Ripple\u2019s global office locations A builder who is able to work autonomously in a fast-paced, dynamic environment A deep personal belief and commitment to diversity and belonging at work What We Offer The chance to work in a fast-paced start-up environment with experienced industry leaders A learning environment where you can dive deep into the latest technologies and make an impact Competitive salary and equity 100% paid medical and dental and 95% paid vision insurance for employees starting on your first day 401k (with match), fully paid parental leave, commuter benefits Generous wellness reimbursement and weekly onsite programs Flexible vacation policy - work with your manager to take time off when you need it Employee giving match Modern office in San Francisco\u2019s Financial District Fully-stocked kitchen with organic snacks, beverages, and coffee drinks Weekly company meeting - ask me anything style discussion with our Leadership Team Team outings to sports games, happy hours, game nights and more! Who We Are Ripple provides one frictionless experience to send money globally using the power of blockchain. By joining Ripple\u2019s growing, global network (RippleNet), financial institutions can process their customers\u2019 payments anywhere in the world instantly, reliably and cost-effectively. Banks and payment providers can use the digital asset XRP to further reduce their costs and access new markets. With offices in San Francisco, New York, London, Mumbai, Singapore, S?o Paulo, Reykjav?k, Washington D.C. and Dubai, Ripple has more than 300 customers around the world. Ripple is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We\u2019re committed to building a diverse and inclusive team. We do not discriminate against qualified employees or applicants because of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference, sexual identity, pregnancy, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, marital status, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, military status, or any other characteristic protected by local law or ordinance. Please find our UK/EU applicant privacy notice here. ", 
